snippet.textDisplay: Mourinho is so overrated. I have stopped watching all his teams play very quickly every time he has been hired somewhere. Inter used to be the most exciting team in Italy until he arrived there and wrecked them. Chelsea was always entertaining. And then Mourinho got there. Same with Man U. Fine, he's won games. But whether these people realize it or not they are in the entertainment business, not the winning business. The two can and often do coincide, but when you're consistently putting a borderline unwatchable product on the field then only your most diehard fans will keep watching. Playing for 1-0 is just a bad plan, period. Especially when you go down early, at which point Mourinho's teams almost always lose. Every time his team loses the world seems a little brighter for me.

snippet.textDisplay:
Ali Moreno, you are a pathetic pundit.
You 'told us so' about Mourinho?

* Since he became Spurs coach, only Liverpool and City have accumulated more points.
* Right now, about 5 key players are missing from his first team. What did you expect to happen against Leipzig?
* You ask to point to a recent example of Mourinho building a team... He took over a Man Utd team that was out of the Champions League. Just because he didn't win the league doesn't mean his time there was a complete failure. He got them back into the Champions League and finished 2nd only to the team which amassed the highest points total in League history. In many other seasons Utd would have won the league that year.


You haven't told us anything mate. You use your own dislike for certain individuals, in this case Mourinho, along with a very short sighted view on football matters as key components in your analysis. Two traits bad pundits have.


Mourinho has been handed a tough job. He has somehow gotten the team to a point where they still have a shot at finishing in the top 4.


You haven't told us anything mate. You are the worst pundit on tv. Get over yourself.

snippet.textDisplay: As a United fan, this is a case of classic Mourinho. He had Spurs playing his Park the bus football even with Kane and Son present. Their absence only gives him more excuses. Who in his right senses will play Tanganga , a young player whose 2 crucial mistakes caused Spurs to lose 2-3 to Wolves in the league, over an experienced defender like Vertonghen? Only the clueless Mourinho who played an inexperienced McTominay in 2018 over our most creative player Paul Pogba against Sevilla at the same stage of the champions league. The result? United were knocked out at Old Trafford after drawing in Sevilla. I'm not a fan of Ole but there's no way Mourinho would have beaten Pep 3 times in a season with his Park the bus football. Ole makes the opposition defense worry about you not just sitting as lambs to be slaughtered. Hopefully United finish off Spurs this Sunday and Mourinho gets fired on Monday. Daniel Levy must cut his losses and fire him quickly.
